  "hint": "Three DFFs form the pipeline stages. Each DFF input comes from a MUX: MUX(sel=Stall, d0=normal_input, d1=current_Q). When Stall=0, data flows forward. When Stall=1, each stage recirculates its own output (freeze). PipeActive = Q1 OR Q2 OR Q3. Inputs: [DataIn, CLK, Stall]. Outputs: [Stage3Out, PipeActive].",
  "title": "3-Stage Pipeline with Stall",
  "objective": "Build a 3-stage pipeline with hazard stall control",
  "description": "Build a 3-stage pipelined datapath (Fetch → Decode → Execute) with a stall signal that freezes the entire pipeline when a data hazard is detected. Each stage uses a MUX to select between advancing (normal) and recirculating (stall). This is how real CPU pipelines handle hazards — the stall signal prevents corrupted data from propagating.",
